history.content:
If you're self-studying math 54 content and are confident in your ability in it, then no need for 16b before 189. I don't believe there's much in 16b for linear algebra that you won't learn in 54. The classes you would be looking for are an advanced class in probability (like EECS 126) and EECS 127, which helps you with both advanced linear algebra and optimization. Neither are strictly mandatory, especially for the spring iteration, but will make your life easier in the class.

As for when you need to take it, it depends on what your goals are. If you want to get ML research in junior fall, then 189 will of course go a long way in helping you get that research. However, it's perfectly normal to take 189 in junior spring (it's a "senior level" course in the first place) so if you don't feel prepared for it yet I definitely wouldn't rush it.

children.subject: I think 127 will be more helpful than 110. 110 didn't help as much as 127

127 is more directly helpful, but there's a fluency in linear algebra that comes though 110 that doesn't with 127 (at least in my case). If you can take only one class of the two while preparing for 189 I'd also recommend 127, but I definitely wouldn't say 110 has no additional benefit to offer.
For 189 purposes it would be better to self study 110 or 127 instead of 54, but in either case if you're taking 189 and 16B together, be cautious about the workload

history.content:
I've already taken math 53 and am self-studying math 54.

I'm hoping to take cs189 next semester, but since I haven't taken ee16b yet, I'm hoping to take them concurrently—but I've seen how people often emphasize that the math 54 (ee16b?) concepts are very important in cs189.

Should I delay taking cs189 until after I've completed 16b, or do you think it's doable taking both classes simultaneously (and doing decently on both)? 

Judging from my personality it seems like I'd much prefer/do better in the spring iterations, so if I don't take it next semester, I feel like I'll take it in spring the following year (my junior year), and I'm wondering if that's a little late (I don't know if I'm being sort of peer-pressured here though since I know quite a few people who have completed cs189 before the end of their sophomore year).
history.subject: when to take cs 189
